Easy Peasy! No Bake White Chocolate Cheesecake

If you are not FOLLOWING ME already -- WHY NOT??!! lol Make sure you click FOLLOW at the top of my page! Rainndroppz.com

INGREDIENTS...
1 cup white chocolate chips
2 (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, cubed & softened
1 (8 ounce) carton Cool Whip
1 9 inch crumb pie crust, any flavor
strawberries or raspberries or blueberries, with sweetened juice

DIRECTIONS

Melt chocolate chips and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in the cool whip until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate until set or overnight.
Serve with your choice of berries on top, preferably with some berry juice, as on shortcake.

Dates in prosciutto
Ingredients
for 10 pieces
10 pitted dates
10 slices of prosciutto
50-70 g. of Gorgonzola
tooth picks
for honey-vinegar sauce
1/4 glass of balsamic vinegar
2 table spoons of honey
a pinch of coarse salt
1/4 tea spoons of black pepper
greens for decoration
Cooking method:
Rolls: Preheat the oven up to 190 degrees. Cut the dates from one side, staff them with grated cheese and roll into prosciutto slices. Pierce the rolls with tooth picks. Lay foil into the roasting tin and put the rolls onto the grill above. Roast for 15-20 minutes.
Honey-vinegar sauce: Mix vinegar, honey, salt and pepper in a small saucepan. At medium heat make it boil and wile the mixture is boiling stir for about 10 minutes until the volume reduces by 75%.
Put the rolls, pour with the sauce, decorate with greens.
Have a good meal!

Shrimp and Pork Jambalaya

Ingredients
1/2 Tbps of Salt
1/2 Tbps cayenne (red pepper)
1/2 Tbps white pepper
1/2 Tbps black pepper
1/2 tsp old bay seasoning
2 or 3 fresh basil leaves chopped
3 medium bay leaves
4 to 5 Cups of chicken stock
1 can of beer (10 or 12 ounce can)
Meats:
1 pound of smoked sausage or andouille - cut in 1/4 inch slices
1 pound of boneless pork country style ribs - cut in 1.5 - 2 inch cubes
1 pound of italian sausage
1 pound of shrimp - peeled and deveined
Vegetables:
1 large onion diced
2 stalks of celery
1 bell pepper diced
3 cloves of garlic diced
Instructions:
1. Heat the pot on medium high heat. Once hot, add the sausage and pork until browned.
2. Remove the meat and add the italian sausage until browned
3. Add the onions, celery, and bellpeppers to the italian sausage and stir until onions are translucent
4. Add Garlic and the beer to deglaze the bottom of the pot (stir to combine)
5. Add all of the seasoning and 1 cup of water (Chicken Stock if you have 5 cups) (mix thoroughly)
6. Cover and cook on medium for 1 hour
7. While thats cooking, peel and de-vein the shrimp
8. Add the Shrimp and cook for 5 minutes
9. Add 4 cups of chicken stock
10. Add 3 cups of uncooked long grain rice.
11. Bring up to a boil - Let boil hard for 5 minutes
12. Reduce heat to the lowest possible setting while maintaining a very low simmer
13. Cook for 30 to 35 minutes.
14. Serve and ENJOY

Recipe:
⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️
*Ingredients*
-3 Chicken Cutlets
-2 cups of Penne Pasta 
-1 1/3 tbs of mild or spicy Jamaican Jerk Sauce Seasoning
-1 Medium Green Bell Pepper (sliced)
-1 Medium Red Bell Pepper (sliced)
-1 Shallot (sliced)
-1 large Garlic Clove (chopped)
-1/2 cup freshly grated Parmesan
-1 cup of Chicken Broth
-1 cup of Heavy Cream
-1 beaten egg
-Flour Mix (Flour, Garlic Powder, Dried Parsley Flakes, Paprika, Salt & Pepper)
-Olive Oil
-Vegetable Oil

*Directions*
Bring water to a boil with some olive oil. Add in uncooked pasta and cook for 15 to 23 minutes. When done, drain pasta and place to the side. In a large non-stick pot, saute shallots & peppers in olive oil. Then add in jerk seasoning. Add in heavy cream and broth and cook until it thickens a little. Add in Parmesan Cheese then cooked pasta, mix and simmer on low heat.  Dip chicken in egg  and then in flour mix to coat completely & repeat for each piece of meat. Heat vegetable oil on high heat in a frying pan. Add in each piece of coated chicken in hot oil. Cook evenly on each side until golden brown. Remove from oil and place on paper towel to soak up oil. Slice each chicken & mix into pasta that is cooking on low heat. Plate then garnish with some freshly grated Parmesan Cheese & serve.
